<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>QMK on Blog</title><link>/tags/qmk/</link><description>Recent content in QMK on Blog</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Sun, 02 Apr 2023 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="/tags/qmk/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>QMK Firmware in M1</title><link>/post/2023/04/02/qmk-firmware-in-m1/</link><pubDate>Sun, 02 Apr 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/post/2023/04/02/qmk-firmware-in-m1/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Running &lt;code&gt;./util/qmk_install.sh&lt;/code&gt; won&amp;rsquo;t work. You need rosetta-enabled terminal session then run these command below:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;$ arch -x86_64 /bin/bash -c &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;$(&lt;/span&gt;curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;$ arch -x86_64 /usr/local/bin/brew install qmk/qmk/qmk
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;After that, &lt;code&gt;qmk&lt;/code&gt; is accessible from anywhere, even from non-rosetta terminal session.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is &lt;a href="https://github.com/herpiko/unk"&gt;UNK&lt;/a&gt; after being flashed directly from a M1 computer:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="/images/2023-04-02-unk.jpg" alt="UNK"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Happy hacking!&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>